-- Kleinwort Benson Names Lombard Odier's Sally Tennant as Chief Executive
-- B y   G a v i n   F i n c h
-- 2010-10-11T08:12:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/kleinwort-benson-names-lombard-odier-s-sally-tennant-as-chief-executive.html
Kleinwort Benson, the U.K. private
bank owned by RHJ International SA, named Sally Tennant chief
executive officer, replacing Robert Taylor.  Tennant joins from Swiss private bank Lombard Odier Darier
Hentsch & Cie., where she ran its U.K. unit, London-based
Kleinwort Benson said in a statement today. Tennant will start
in mid-January. RHJ, the publicly traded investment company
started by Timothy Collins, acquired Kleinwort Benson in July.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gavin Finch in London at 
 gfinch@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at 
 eevans3@bloomberg.net  